.tgz","fileCount":17,"unpackedSize":1900019,"signatures":[{"keyid":"SHA256:DhQ8wR5APBvFHLF/+Tc+AYvPOdTpcIDqOhxsBHRwC7U","sig":"MEUCIQC6g/lwEOpyq54dg6AP4VGt+4XagTatpLBGSubcHKdJUQIgDQst9XMR7srSNLtQzPonefDMiGn76dcml84pRVBUSdo="}]},"_npmUser":{"name":"swagger-api","email":"apiteam@swagger.io"},"directories":{},"maintainers":[{"name":"swagger-api","email":"apiteam@swagger.io"}],"_npmOperationalInternal":{"host":"s3://npm-registry-packages-npm-production","tmp":"tmp/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2_1.10.2_1776077050874_0.09570361431012864"},"_hasShrinkwrap":false}},"time":{"created":"2026-02-27T09:10:50.455Z","modified":"2026-04-13T10:44:11.203Z","1.6.0":"2026-02-27T09:10:50.766Z","1.7.0":"2026-03-17T13:02:05.853Z","1.8.0":"2026-03-20T14:09:23.719Z","1.9.0":"2026-03-30T10:45:53.173Z","1.10.0":"2026-04-01T11:13:55.959Z","1.10.1":"2026-04-07T12:53:48.674Z","1.10.2":"2026-04-13T10:44:11.094Z"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/issues"},"author":{"name":"SmartBear"},"license":"Apache-2.0","homepage":"https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom#readme","repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom.git"},"description":"Parser adapter for parsing YAML 1.2 documents into OpenAPI 3.2.x namespace.","maintainers":[{"name":"swagger-api","email":"apiteam@swagger.io"}],"readme":"# @swagger-api/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2\n\n\\`@swagger-api/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2\\` is a parser adapter for the [OpenAPI 3.2.0 specification](https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/main/versions/3.2.0.md) in [YAML 1.2 format](https://yaml.org/spec/1.2.2/).\nUnder the hood this adapter uses [apidom-parser-adapter-yaml-1-2](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-parser-adapter-yaml-1-2)\nto parse a source string into generic ApiDOM in [base ApiDOM namespace](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-core#base-namespace)\nwhich is then refracted with [OpenAPI 3.2.0 Refractors](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-ns-openapi-3-2#refractors).\n\n## Installation\n\nAfter [prerequisites](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/blob/main/README.md#prerequisites) for installing this package are satisfied, you can install it\nvia [npm CLI](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli) by running the following command:\n\n\\`\\`\\`sh\n $ npm install @swagger-api/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Parser adapter API\n\nThis parser adapter is fully compatible with parser adapter interface required by [@swagger-api/apidom-parser](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-parser#mounting-parser-adapters)\nand implements all required properties.\n\n### mediaTypes\n\nDefines list of media types that this parser adapter recognizes.\n\n\\`\\`\\`js\n[\n  'application/vnd.oai.openapi;version=3.2.0',\n  'application/vnd.oai.openapi+yaml;version=3.2.0',\n]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### detect\n\n[Detection](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/blob/main/packages/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2/src/adapter.ts#L15) is based on a regular expression matching required OpenAPI 3.2.x specification symbols in YAML format.\n\n### namespace\n\nThis adapter exposes an instance of [OpenAPI 3.2.x ApiDOM namespace](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-ns-openapi-3-2#openapi-32x-namespace).\n\n### parse\n\n\\`parse\\` function consumes various options as a second argument. Here is a list of these options:\n\nOption | Type | Default | Description\n--- | --- | --- | ---\n<a name=\"specObj\"></a>\\`specObj\\` | \\`Object\\` | [Specification Object](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/blob/main/packages/apidom-ns-openapi-3-2/src/refractor/specification.ts) | This specification object drives the YAML AST transformation to OpenAPI 3.2.x ApiDOM namespace.\n<a name=\"sourceMap\"></a>\\`sourceMap\\` | \\`Boolean\\` | \\`false\\` | Indicate whether to generate source maps.\n<a name=\"refractorOpts\"></a>\\`refractorOpts\\` | \\`Object\\` | \\`{}\\` | Refractor options are [passed to refractors](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-ns-openapi-3-2#refractor-plugins) during refracting phase.\n\nAll unrecognized arbitrary options will be ignored.\n\n## Usage\n\nThis parser adapter can be used directly or indirectly via [@swagger-api/apidom-parser](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-parser).\n\n### Direct usage\n\nDuring direct usage you don't need to provide \\`mediaType\\` as the \\`parse\\` function is already pre-bound\nwith [supported media types](#mediatypes).\n\n\\`\\`\\`js\nimport { parse, detect } from '@swagger-api/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2';\n\n// detecting\nawait detect('openapi: 3.2.0'); // => true\nawait detect('openapi: 3.1.0'); // => false\nawait detect('test'); // => false\n\n// parsing\nconst parseResult = await parse('openapi: 3.2.0', { sourceMap: true });\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Indirect usage\n\nYou can omit the \\`mediaType\\` option here, but please read [Word on detect vs mediaTypes](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/tree/main/packages/apidom-parser#word-on-detect-vs-mediatypes) before you do so.\n\n\\`\\`\\`js\nimport ApiDOMParser from '@swagger-api/apidom-parser';\nimport * as openApiYamlAdapter from '@swagger-api/apidom-parser-adapter-openapi-yaml-3-2';\n\nconst parser = new ApiDOMParser();\n\nparser.use(openApiYamlAdapter);\n\nconst parseResult = await parser.parse('openapi: 3.2.0', { mediaType: openApiYamlAdapter.mediaTypes.latest('yaml') });\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## License\n\n[Apache-2.0](https://github.com/swagger-api/apidom/blob/main/LICENSE)\n","readmeFilename":"README.md"}